      'Prisma is a modern, type-safe ORM (Object-Relational Mapping) for Node.js and TypeScript that simplifies database access with auto-generated, type-safe query builders. Prisma supports PostgreSQL, MySQL, SQLite, SQL Server, MongoDB, and CockroachDB. Prisma 5 introduced significant performance improvements, JSON protocol for faster queries, and improved serverless support with smaller bundle sizes.\n\nPrisma consists of three core components: Prisma Schema for defining data models in a declarative DSL, Prisma Client for type-safe database queries generated from the schema, and Prisma Migrate for managing database schema migrations. The schema file serves as the single source of truth for the database structure, and running prisma generate creates a fully typed client with auto-completion for all models, fields, and relations.\n\nPrisma type-safe queries catch errors at compile time rather than runtime, significantly reducing bugs in database interactions. The query builder supports filtering, pagination, sorting, relation loading (similar to eager/lazy loading), aggregations, transactions, and raw SQL when needed. Prisma Studio provides a visual database browser for inspecting and editing data. Prisma integrates seamlessly with Next.js, NestJS, Express, Fastify, and GraphQL frameworks.',
