      'Mongoose is the most popular ODM (Object Document Mapper) for MongoDB and Node.js, providing a schema-based solution to model application data. Mongoose adds a layer of structure to MongoDB flexible document model through schemas, validators, middleware, and query builders. With over 26,000 GitHub stars and billions of npm downloads, Mongoose is the standard tool for MongoDB interaction in Node.js applications.\n\nMongoose schemas define document structure with field types, validation rules, default values, and virtual properties. The middleware system (pre/post hooks) enables automatic actions on save, validate, remove, and query operations for concerns like password hashing, audit logging, and data transformation. Population (similar to SQL joins) resolves referenced documents across collections.\n\nMongoose provides a rich query API with chainable methods for filtering, sorting, pagination, field selection, and aggregation pipeline building. The discriminator feature enables single-collection inheritance for polymorphic documents. Mongoose 8.x brought improved TypeScript support with schema-inferred types, performance optimizations, and better lean query handling for read-heavy workloads.',
